also the moduli  now also can be naturally negative. In fact, if
we take a real potential  and hermitian matrices , then
the eigenvalues of positive charge will typically sit at the (stable)
minima, while those of negative charge will sit at the (unstable)
maxima.

Note that the -cycle period



have an interpretation as either removing a positively charged
eigenvalue from the system, or adding a negatively charged one.  The
system is therefore insensitive to adding an
eigenvalue/anti-eigenvalue pair.  So the planar free energy  of
quiver matrix model, as a function of the variables , is exactly
the same as that of the one-matrix model. In fact, since the full loop
equations for  are identical to those of the one-matrix model,
this identity holds also for the higher genus contributions .

