23  A_i A_j A_k)].
 

The second term is just the holomorphic Chern-Simons action on the
manifold . Note that the variation of the Chern-Simons term is the
(holomorphic) curvature , so that after integrating out the
auxiliary fields the action contains the term 
which produces exactly the internal part of the Yang-Mills term.

There is of course also a D-term, that is in this case given by
